## [CRITICAL] Version Constraints — DO NOT MODIFY

- PHP: 8.4.18 (FORBIDDEN: upgrade to 8.5+)
- Laravel: 11.51.0 (FORBIDDEN: major update)
- Filament: 3.3.49 (FORBIDDEN: v4 API or Schema patterns)
- composer.json: NEVER change versions without explicit user approval
- Sail runtime path: ./vendor/laravel/sail/runtimes/8.4 (fixed, do not alter)
- compose.yaml: preserve structure and indentation exactly

## [RULE] Color contrast (always)

- Every background MUST have explicit foreground colors that remain readable in both light and dark (use `text-gray-950 dark:text-white` or a dedicated palette such as `bg-slate-900` + `text-slate-100`).
- Never leave body text as default without checking: `bg-white` + `text-gray-900` / `dark:bg-gray-900` + `text-gray-100` (or equivalent) on the same element or its text children.
- Custom modals/panels: either force a single contrast context (e.g. `dark` + dark `!bg-*` + light text) or duplicate Filament’s light/dark pairs; do not mix white Filament surfaces with theme-dependent text that can match the background.
- After UI changes, mentally verify: light mode AND dark mode — no “invisible” text on tables, inputs, badges, or nested `fi-section` cards.

## [RULE] Filament v3 Frontend

- USE: x-filament::_ and x-filament-tables::_ official Blade components
- FORBIDDEN: custom <div>/<table> layouts, inline styles, <style> tags
- CSS: Tailwind utility classes only
- DO NOT break Filament-generated class structures (fi-section, fi-input-wrp, etc.)

## [RULE] Compact UI

- Reduce default spacing by one step (e.g. gap-y-4 → gap-y-2)
- Remove empty fi-section-header via header(null)
- Prefer table layout over card layout for list views
- Use grid for horizontal input layout; avoid tall vertical pages
- Responsive grid: grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3

## [RULE] Robustness

- Live inputs: wire:model.live.debounce.500ms required
- Numeric inputs: numeric + step="0.001"
- Images/large elements: aspect-video + overflow-hidden
- On layout issues: replace custom implementation with standard Filament components first

## [RULE] Frontend Layout Safety (No-Drift)

- One page, one CSS ecosystem: NEVER mix Bootstrap and Tailwind on the same page.
- If a page uses any `x-filament::*` component, ALWAYS include `@filamentStyles` and `@filamentScripts(withCore: true)`.
- Keep Tailwind syntax version consistent per project setup (do not mix v3/v4 utility names).
- Prefer `@vite(resources/css/app.css)` for stable class generation; use CDN only when explicitly required.
- Keep layout responsibilities isolated (e.g. `timecard` layout must not depend on Bootstrap-only nav/modal components).
- Standardize form controls: use consistent classes for `input/select/textarea`; for `select`, enforce `appearance-none` + custom arrow.
- Keep Alpine.js local and minimal (`x-data` scoped per section; use `x-show` + `x-collapse` for toggles).
- Do not put complex data logic in Blade; compute in Controller/Livewire and pass view-ready data.
- Before finalizing UI changes, verify mobile (390px) and tablet (768px) for: initial render, input, error state, modal state, and navigation.
- Final grep check for Tailwind pages: no `btn-`, `row`, `col-`, `data-bs-`, or Bootstrap CDN links.

## [RULE] TALL Stack Hydration & State Safety (Guest UI)

- FORBIDDEN: Injecting JSON data (`@json`, `@js`) directly into HTML attributes like `x-data` or `x-init`. It causes double-quote collision and DOM breakage.
- REQUIRED: Use `<script type="application/json" id="data-xxx">` to pass large PHP arrays/objects to the frontend safely.
- FORBIDDEN: `import Alpine from 'alpinejs'` in standard JS files when using Livewire 3 (causes double instantiation).
- REQUIRED: Extend Alpine only via `document.addEventListener('alpine:init', () => { window.Alpine.store(...) })`.
- REQUIRED: Ensure Tailwind v4 content scanning is configured via `@source` in `resources/css/app.css`, not `tailwind.config.js`.
